{"title_page": "List of Marasmiaceae genera", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe [[Marasmiaceae]] are a [[family (biology)|family]] of [[fungi]] in the order [[Agaricales]]. It includes over 50 [[genera]] and some 1590 [[species]].<ref name=Kirk2008>{{cite book |vauthors=Kirk PM, Cannon PF, Minter DW, Stalpers JA |title=Dictionary of the Fungi |edition=10th |publisher=CABI |location=Wallingford, UK |year=2008 |page=401 |isbn=0-85199-826-7}}</ref>\n\n==Genera==\n[[File:Marasmius rotula 46829.jpg|thumb|''[[Marasmius rotula]]'']]\n[[File:Pluteus spec. - Lindsey 1a.jpg|thumb|''[[Megacollybia platyphylla]]'']]\n[[File:Shiitakegrowing.jpg|thumb|''[[Lentinula edodes]]'']]\n[[File:Campanella 72075.jpg|thumb|''[[Campanells]]'' sp.]]\n[[File:Tetrapyrgos nigripes 53251.jpg|thumb|''[[Tetrapyrgos nigripes]]'']]\n[[File:Marasmiellus ramealis - Lindsey.jpg|thumb|''[[Marasmiellus ramealis]]'']]\n[[File:Omphalotus olearius 33857.jpg|thumb|''[[Omphalotus olearius]]'']]\n[[File:Anthracophyllum archeri 30124.jpg|thumb|''[[Anthracophyllum archeri]]'']]\n[[File:Collybia maculata1.jpg|thumb|''[[Rhodocollybia maculata]]'']]\n[[File:Henningsomyces candidus 81761.jpg|thumb|''[[Henningsomyces candidus]]'']]\n[[File:Crinipellis zonata 97845.jpg|thumb|''[[Crinipellis zonata]]'']]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n!  Genus !!  Year !! class=\"unsortable\" | [[Type species]] !!# of species!!class=\"unsortable\"|Distribution\n|-\n| align=left |''[[Amyloflagellula]]''<br/><small>[[Rolf Singer|Singer]]<ref name=singer1966/></small>\n|1908\n|''[[Amyloflagellula pulchra]]''<br/><small>([[Miles Joseph Berkeley|Berk.]] & Broome) Singer</small>\n|4\n|Asia, Neotropics\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Anastrophella]]''<br/><small>E.Horak & Desjardin<ref name=horak-desjardin1994/></small>\n|1994\n|''[[Anastrophella subpeltata]]''<br/><small>(Redhead) E.Horak & Desjardin</small>\n|3\n|New Zealand, Japan, Hawaii\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Anthracophyllum]]''<br/><small>[[Ces.]]<ref name=cesati1879/></small>\n|1879\n|''[[Anthracophyllum beccarianum]]''<br/><small>Ces.</small>\n|10\n|Tropical Asia and America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Aphyllotus]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1973/></small>\n|1974<br/>(\"1973\")<ref group=N>Conventional mean to indicate that the taxonomic date of publication for the purpose of [[Principle of Priority|priority]] is different from the date given by the work itself.</ref>\n|''Aphyllotus campanelliformis''<br/><small>Singer</small>\n|1\n|Colombia\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Baeospora]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1938/></small>\n|1938\n|''[[Baeospora myosura]]''<br/><small>([[Elias Magnus Fries|Fr.]]:Fr.) Singer</small>\n|10\n|Worldwide\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Calathella]]''<ref group=N>This illegitimate name is a later homonym of a genus of fossil algae (Florin, ''Senckenbergiana'' '''11''':241\u2013266, 1929). The genus also appears to be polyphyletic, but the affinities of its type species are currently unknown, leaving its final placement uncertain (Yamaguchi et al., ''Mycoscience'' '''50'''(3)156\u2013164, 2009; Sulzbacher & al., ''Mycotaxon'' '''105''':37\u201342, 2008).</ref><br/><small>[[D.A.Reid]]<ref name=reid1964/></small>\n|1964\n|''[[Calathella eruciformis]]''<br/><small> (P.Micheli ex [[Batsch]]) D.A.Reid</small>\n|9\n|Europe, North America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Calyptella]]''<br/><small>[[Qu\u00e9l.]]<ref name=quelet1884/></small>\n|1886\n|''[[Calyptella capula]]''<br/><small>([[Holmsk.]]) Qu\u00e9l.</small>\n|20\n|Cosmopolitan\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Campanella (fungus)|Campanella]]''<br/><small>[[Henn.]]<ref name=hennings1895/></small>\n|1895\n|''[[Campanella buettneri]]''<br/><small>Henn.</small>\n|~40\n|Cosmopolitan, but mostly tropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Caripia]]''<br/><small>[[Otto Kuntze|Kuntze]]<ref name=kuntze1898/></small>\n|1898\n|''Caripia montagnei''<br/><small>(Berk.) Kuntze</small>\n|1\n|Neotropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Cephaloscypha]]''<br/><small>Agerer<ref name=agerer1975/></small>\n|1975\n(\"1974\")\n|''Cephaloscypha morlichensis''<br/><small>(W.B.Cooke) Agerer</small>\n|1\n|Worldwide\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Chaetocalathus]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1943/></small>\n|1943\n|''[[Chaetocalathus craterellus]]''<br/><small>([[Michel Charles Durieu de Maisonneuve|Durieu]] & [[L\u00e9v.]]) Singer</small>\n|~20\n|Mostly subtropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Clitocybula]]''<br/><small>(Singer) Singer ex M\u00e9trod<ref name=metrod1952/></small>\n|1952\n|''[[Clitocybula lacerata]]''<br/><small>([[Scopoli]]) Singer ex M\u00e9trod</small>\n|~15\n|Cosmopolitan in temperate areas\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Connopus]]''<br/><small>[[Ron Petersen|R.H.Petersen]]<ref name=Hughes2010/></small>\n|2010\n|''Connopus acervatus''<br/><small>(Fr.:Fr.) R.H.Petersen</small>\n|1\n|Europe, North America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Crinipellis]]''<br/><small>[[Pat.]]<ref name=Patouillard1889/></small>\n|1889\n|''Crinipellis stipitaria''<ref group=N>This species' type is now considered to fall within ''[[Crinipellis scabella]]''.</ref><br/><small>(Fr.:Fr.) Pat.</small>\n|~75\n|Worldwide, mostly tropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Cymatella]]''<br/><small>Pat.<ref name=Patouillard1899/></small>\n|1899\n|''[[Cymatella minima]]''<br/><small>Pat.</small>\n|4\n|Antilles\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Cymatellopsis]]''<br/><small>Parmasto<ref name=parmasto1984/></small>\n|1985<br/>(\"1984\") \n|''Cymatellopsis ilmiana''<br/><small></small>\n|1\n|Africa\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Deigloria]]''<br/><small>Agerer<ref name=agerer1980/></small>\n|1980\n|''[[Deigloria pulchella]]''<br/><small>Agerer</small>\n|10\n|Neotropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Epicnaphus]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1960/></small>\n|1960\n|''[[Epicnaphus phalaropus]]''<br/><small>Singer</small>\n|3\n|South America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Fissolimbus]]''<br/><small>E.Horak<ref name=horak1979/></small>\n|1979\n|''Fissolimbus fallaciosus''<br/><small>E.Horak</small>\n|1\n|Papua New Guinea\n|-\n|align=lef