us]]''<br/><small>([[Batsch]]) Singer</small>\n|~100\n|Mostly tropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Hymenogloea]]''<br/><small>Pat.<ref name=patouillard1900/></small>\n|1900\n|''Hymenogloea riofrioi''<br/><small>(Pat.) Pat.</small>\n|1\n|Tropical Americas\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Lactocollybia]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1938-SZP/></small>\n|1939<br/>(\"1938\")\n|''[[Lactocollybia lacrimosa]]''<br/><small>(R.Heim) Singer</small>\n|17\n|Primarily tropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Lecanocybe]]''<br/><small>Desjardin & E.Horak<ref name=desjardin-horak1999/></small>\n|1999\n|''Lecanocybe lateralis''<br/><small>Desjardin & E.Horak</small>\n|1\n|Java, Hawaii\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Lentinula]]''<br/><small>[[Franklin Sumner Earle|Earle]]<ref name=earle1906/></small>\n|1909<br/>(\"1906\")\n|''Lentinula cubensis''<ref group=N>A synonym of ''[[Lentinula boryana]]''.</ref><br/><small>([[Berk.]] & M.A.Curtis) Earle</small>\n|3/5<ref group=N>Depending on the circumscription of Asian species.</ref>\n|East Asia, North and Central America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Macrocystidia]]''<br/><small>Joss.<ref name=josserand1933/></small>\n|1934<br/>(\"1933\")\n|''[[Macrocysitidia cucumis]]''<br/><small>(Pers.:Fr.) Joss.</small>\n|5\n|Worldwide\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Manuripia]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1960/></small>\n|1960\n|''Manuripia bifida''<br/><small>Singer</small>\n|1\n|Bolivia\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Marasmiellus]]''<br/><small>[[William Murrill|Murrill]]<ref name=murrill1915/></small>\n|1915\n|''[[Marasmiellus juniperinus]]''<br/><small>Murrill</small>\n|~250\n|Cosmopolitan\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Marasmius]]''<br/><small>Fr.<ref name=fries1836/></small>\n|1836<br/>(\"1835\")\n|''[[Marasmius rotula]]''<br/><small>([[Scop.]]:Fr.) Fr.</small>\n|~500\n|Worldwide\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Megacollybia]]''<br/><small>Kotl.<ref name=kotlaba1972/></small>\n|1972\n|''[[Megacollybia platyphylla]]''<br/><small>(Pers.:Fr.) [[Franti\u0161ek Kotlaba|Kotl.]] & Pouzar</small>\n|8+\n|Europe, Eastern No