.A.Reid) Singer</small>\n|1\n|Sierra Leone\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Phaeodepas]]''<br/><small>D.A.Reid<ref name=reid1961/></small>\n|1961\n|''[[Phaeodepas dennisii]]''<br/><small>D.A.Reid</small>\n|2\n|Venezuela\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Pleurocybella]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1947/></small>\n|1947\n|''Pleurocybella porrigens''<br/><small>(Pers.:Fr.) Singer</small>\n|1\n|Worldwide, northern temperate\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Pseudotyphula]]''<br/><small>[[E. J. H. Corner|Corner]]<ref name=corner1953/></small>\n|1953\n|''Pseudotyphula ochracea''<br/><small>Corner</small>\n|1\n|North America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Rectipilus]]''<br/><small>Agerer<ref name=agerer1973/></small>\n|1973\n|''[[Rectipilus fascinculatus]]''<br/><small>(Pers.:Fr.) Agerer</small>\n|9\n|Cosmopolitan\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Rhodocollybia]]''<br/><small>Singer<ref name=singer1938-SZP/></small>\n|1939<br/>(\"1938\")\n|''[[Rhodocollybia maculata]]''<br/><small>([[Alb.]] & [[Schwein.]]:Fr.) Singer</small>\n|~30\n|Americas, Europe\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Skepperiella]]''<br/><small>[[Albert Pil\u00e1t|Pil\u00e1t]]<ref name=pilat1927/></small>\n|1927\n|''[[Skepperiella spathularia]]''<br/><small>(Berk. & M.A.Curtis) [[Albert Pil\u00e1t|Pil\u00e1t]]</small>\n|4\n|Cosmopolitan\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Stipitocyphella]]''<ref group=N>Because the type appears to remain in the author's private collection, it is not clear whether the publication is considered valid under the [[International Code of Botanical Nomenclature]].</ref><br/><small>G.Kost<ref name=kost1998/></small>\n|1998\n|''Stipitocyphella kenyensis''<br/><small>G. Kost</small>\n|1\n|East Africa\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Stromatocyphella]]''<br/><small>W.B.Cooke<ref name=cooke1961/></small>\n|1961\n|''[[Stromatocyphella conglobata]]''<br/><small>(Burt) W.B.Cooke</small>\n|3\n|North America\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Tetrapyrgos]]''<ref group=N>A replacement name for Georges M\u00e9trod's ''Pterospora'' (''Les Myc\u00e8nes de Madagascar'':129, 1949), which was already in use as ''[[Pterospora]]'' [[Nutt.]] (''Gen. N. Amer. Pl.'' '''1''':269,  1818).</ref><br/><small>E.Horak<ref name=horak1987/></small>\n|1987\n|''[[Tetrapyrgos atrocyanea]]''<br/><small>(M\u00e9trod) E.Horak</small>\n|16\n|Worldwide, mostly tropical\n|-\n|align=left| ''[[Trogia]]''<br/><small>Fr.<ref name=fries1836/></small>\n|1836\n|''[[Trogia aplorutis]]''<br/><small>(Mont.) Fr.</small>\n|~20\n|Widespread, mostly tropical\n|}\n\n==Notes and references==\n;Notes\n{{reflist|group=N}}\n;References\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n<ref name=agerer1973>{{cite journal |last=Agerer |first=R. |year=1973 |title=''Rectipilus'', eine neue Gattung cyphelloider Pilze |journal=Persoonia |volume=7 |issue= |pages=389\u2013436 |doi=|language=German |trans-title=''Rectipilus'', a New Genus of Cyphelloid Fungi}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=agerer1975>{{cite journal |last=Agerer |first=R. |year=1973\u20131974 |title=''Flagelloscypha''. Studien an cyphelloiden Basidiomyceten. |journal=Sydowia |volume=27 |issue=1\u20136 |pages=131\u2013265 |doi=|language=German |trans-title=Studies on Cyphelloid Basidiomycetes. ''Flagelloscypha''}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=agerer1980>{{cite journal |last=Agerer |first= R. |year=1980 |title=Contribution to neotropical cyphellaceous fungi - II. ''Deigloria'' gen.nov. (Physalacriaceae). |journal=Mycotaxon |volume=12 |issue=1 |pages=185\u2013200 |url=http://www.cybertruffle.org.uk/cyberliber/59575/0012/001/0185.htm}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=agerer1983>{{cite journal |last=Agerer |first=R. |year=1983 |title=Beitrag zur Flora cyphelloider Pilze aus der Neotropis V. Zwei neue Gattungen: ''Metulocyphella'' und ''Incrustocalyptella'' |journal=Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Mykologie |volume=49 |issue=2 |pages=155\u2013164 |doi=|language=German |trans-title=Contribution to neotropical cyphellaceous fungi V. Two new genera: ''Metulocyphella'' and ''Incrustocalyptella''}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=agerer1983-MBS>{{cite journal |last=Agerer |first=R. |year=1983 |title=Typusstudien an cyphelloiden Pilzen I