ey.cnn.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201045348/http://money.cnn.com/1999/11/04/deals/drug_deal/|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"washingtonpost.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/pmextra/nov99/4/pfizer.htm|title=Pfizer Makes Bid for Warner-Lambert (washingtonpost.com)|website=www.washingtonpost.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411055406/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/pmextra/nov99/4/pfizer.htm|archive-date=11 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1999/11/05/business/warner-lambert-gets-pfizer-offer-for-82.4-billion.html|title=WARNER-LAMBERT GETS PFIZER OFFER FOR $82.4 BILLION|first1=David J.|last1=Morrow|first2=Laura M.|last2=Holson|date=5 November 1999|accessdate=22 November 2017|via=www.nytimes.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213161204/http://www.nytimes.com/1999/11/05/business/warner-lambert-gets-pfizer-offer-for-82.4-billion.html|archive-date=13 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 16\n| 1999\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[Deutsche Telekom]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Telecom Italia]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|81.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|81|1999}}\n| [[Olivetti]] was able to sway key Telecom Italia shareholders and win control of 51% of shares, killing the proposed merger of the telecommunication giants.<ref>https://www.wired.com/1999/05/deutsche-telekom-gets-dumped/</ref><ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/348931.stm</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 17\n| 2014\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[21st Century Fox]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Time Warner]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|80.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|80|2014}}\n| 21st Century Fox abandoned its takeover of Time Warner Inc., due to the unwillingness of the Time Warner Board to engage with the Fox executives