lan in $40.1B Cash-And-Stock Deal |date=April 21, 2015 |accessdate=April 21, 2015 |work=[[Pharma. Process.|Pharmaceutical Processing]] |url=http://www.pharmpro.com/news/2015/04/teva-offers-buy-mylan-401b-cash-and-stock-deal?et_cid=4527542&et_rid=280926499&location=top |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421225023/http://www.pharmpro.com/news/2015/04/teva-offers-buy-mylan-401b-cash-and-stock-deal?et_cid=4527542&et_rid=280926499&location=top |archive-date=April 21, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Mylan stated in June 2015 that Teva\u2019s disclosure that it had a 1.35 percent stake in Mylan violated [[US]] anti-trust rules.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 43\n| 2011\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[AT&T]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[T-Mobile US]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 39.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|39|2011}}\n| On August 31, 2011, the [[United States Department of Justice Antitrust Division|Antitrust Division]] of the [[United States Department of Justice]] formally announced that it would seek to block the takeover, and filed a lawsuit to such effect in federal court.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-08-31/u-s-files-antitrust-complaint-to-block-proposed-at-t-t-mobile-merger|title=T-Mobile Antitrust Challenge Gives AT&T Little Recourse|via=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2017-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910020052/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-08-31/u-s-files-antitrust-complaint-to-block-proposed-at-t-t-mobile-merger|archive-date=2017-09-10|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 44\n| 2019\n| {{flagicon|HKG}} [[Hong Kong Stock Exchange]] \n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[London Stock Exchange]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 39.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|39|2019}}\n| $39 billion takeover proposal was rejected by the Board of the London Stock Exchange.<ref>https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-lse-m-a-hkexlse/hong-kong-exchange-vows-to-press-on