19\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Altria]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Philip Morris International]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|200.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|200|2019}}\n|The merger was called off after a chilly reaction from investors, vaping related illnesses, and Altria's increasingly scrutinized $12.8 billion investment in vaping leader [[JUUL]].<ref>https://www.cnbc.com/2019/09/25/philip-morris-and-altria-end-merger-talks.html</ref> \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\n| 2015\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Pfizer]]\n| {{flagicon|IRL}}{{flagicon|USA}} [[Allergan, plc]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|160.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|160|2015}}\n|The deal fell through over changes made to [[tax inversion]] legislation by the [[US Government]].<ref name=\"wolfstreet.com\">{{cite web|url=http://wolfstreet.com/2016/04/07/end-of-boom-failed-us-mergers-acquisitions-2016-all-time-record/|title=M&A Boom Implodes, US Deal Failures in 2016 Worst Ever|date=7 April 2016|access-date=22 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923041913/http://wolfstreet.com/2016/04/07/end-of-boom-failed-us-mergers-acquisitions-2016-all-time-record/|archive-date=23 September 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> \n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n| 2008\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} {{flagicon|AUS}} [[BHP Billiton]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Rio Tinto Group|Rio Tinto]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|148.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|148|2008}}\n| As commodity prices fell in value, the deal became too risky for BHP Billiton to complete.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB122759796497756137|title=Death of a Megadeal: BHP Ends Its Pursuit of Rio|first1=Robert Guy|last1=Matthews|first2=Dana|last2=Cimilluca|first3=Patrick|last3=Barta|date=26 November 2008|via=Wall Street Journal|access-date=18 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219012251/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB122759796497756137|archiv