{"title_page": "List of churches in the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Francisco", "text_new": "This is a list of current and former [[Roman Catholicism in the United States|Roman Catholic]] churches in the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Francisco]]. The Archdiocese of San Francisco includes the [[San Francisco, California|City and County of San Francisco]] and the Counties of [[Marin County, California|Marin]] and [[San Mateo County, California|San Mateo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Parish Finder|publisher=Archdiocese of San Francisco|accessdate=April 19, 2020|url=https://sfarchdiocese.org/parishfinder?query=marin&#37;20county}}</ref> The archdiocese includes many historic churches including [[Mission San Francisco de As\u00eds]], the oldest building in San Francisco, and [[Saints Peter and Paul Church, San Francisco|Saints Peter and Paul Church]], known as the Italian cathedral of the West.\n\n==San Francisco County==\n===Deanery 1===\nDeanery 1 consists of San Francisco's [[Sunset District]], Forest Hill, Parkside, Westwood Park, and Lakeside neighborhoods.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Name'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"10%\" |'''Image'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Location'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"15\" |'''Description/Notes'''\n|-\n|[[Holy Name of Jesus Church in San Francisco|Holy Name of Jesus]]\n|[[File:Holy Name of Jesus Church (San Francisco).jpg|100px]]\n|1555 39th Avenue\n|Parish created in 1925 in the [[Sunset District]]; the current modern concrete and steel church was dedicated in 1964 and was referred to at the time as being \"as modern as tomorrow\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Church History|publisher=Holy Name of Jesus Parish|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://holynamesf.org/index.php/about/church-history}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[St. Anne of the Sunset Church in San Francisco|St. Anne of the Sunset]]\n|[[File:St. Anne of the Sunset.jpg|100px]]\n|850 Judah St.\n|Romanesque church in [[Sunset District]] completed in 1932\n|-\n|[[St. Brendan Church in San Francisco|St. Brendan the Navigator]]\n|\n|29 Rockaway Ave.\n|California mission-style structure with a distinctive bell tower<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=St. Brendan the Navigator Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=http://www.stbrendanparish.org/}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[St. Cecilia Church in San Francisco|St. Cecilia]]\n|\n|2555 17th Ave\n|Parish created in 1917; current Spanish colonial church completed in 1956 in [[Sunset District]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Saint Ceclia Parish History|publisher=Saint Cecilia Catholic Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://stcecilia.com/parish-life/about}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Finn Barr\n|\n|415 Edna Street\n|Parish created in 1926 in the Sunnyside district<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to Our Parish|publisher=St. Finn Barr Catholic Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://sfbsf.org/}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Gabriel\n|\n|2559 40th Avenue\n|Parish established in 1941; church dedicated in 1942<ref>{{cite web|title=History of St. Gabriel|publisher=St. Gabriel Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.sgparish.org/history.html}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. John of God\n|\n|1290 5th Ave\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=St. John of God Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.sjog.net/}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Stephen\n|\n|601 Eucalyptus Dr\n|Parish formed in 1950; new church dedicated in 1964<ref>{{cite web|title=Excerpt from \"Saint Stephen Parish Celebrates Fifty Years\"|publisher=Saint Stephen Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.saintstephensf.org/our-history.php}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Thomas More\n|\n|1300 Junipero Serra Blvd\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=St. Thomas More Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://stmchurch.com/}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Deanery 2===\nDeanery 2 consists of the [[Bayview-Hunters Point, 